Ah, almost forgot! I don't know about the - on Astrotrain. I wouldn't 
say that's enough difference, but I guess it might be.

::Killfest::

Killfest nods, sizing Astrotrain up. "Hmm.. That would be benificial 
to both of us, yes.."

He considers something for a second, looking into the foliage around. 
He had a feeling he was being watched, but it wasn't important right 
now. He looks back at Astrotrain.

"I agree to those terms. What information do you seek?"




--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, "rAuq" <rauq@t...> wrote:
> "Yes, an aliance would be good, we're new here... and it has 
> appeared obvious that we are quite out numbered, forcing some 
> sort of union to help even the odds. We are prepared to help you in 
> exchange for some information and protection." replyes Astro-Train 
> at great length. He looks calculatingly at Killfest as he talks.
